# Internationalization

Every user-facing string lives in `app/i18n.py` and is rendered through
the `_('key')` Jinja global (or `gettext('key', language)` in Python).
Never hardcode English or German prose in templates, route handlers,
service modules, or error messages.

The catalogue is bilingual: every key has both an English value (in the
EN section) and a German value (in the DE section). Adding one without
the other is a regression.

## Error messages

Error pages and `HTTPException(detail=...)` payloads are user-facing.
Make the message self-contained so no English fragments leak into a
German session, and key it under `error.{domain}.{condition}`.
